WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.500
Four clinical imperatives.

00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:05.000
First — suspect myocarditis in any young

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.500
patient with unexplained heart failure, troponin elevation,

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:09.500
or arrhythmia.

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:13.000
Second — cardiac MRI is your most

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.000
powerful non-invasive diagnostic tool.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.500
Third — biopsy when hemodynamics or rhythm

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:21.500
demand it — histology changes therapy.

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:24.000
Fourth — etiology determines treatment.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.500
Giant cell and ICI myocarditis require aggressive

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:28.000
immunosuppression.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Early recognition saves lives.
